    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-07-19T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-07-19T17:00:00-05:00" n="195"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d195">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3940: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Des Fortes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-07-19T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 19, 1934—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:07 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>42. Department’s telegram No. 11.<note n="6" xml:id="d195fn6">July 18, 2 p.m.,
                            <ref target="#pg_149">p. 149</ref>.</note> Argentine Minister called on
                    Foreign Minister this afternoon, explained there that Paraguay was given point 1
                    of the proposal previously because it concerns forceful acquisition of territory
                    declaration of August, ’32.<note n="7" xml:id="d195fn7">
                        <ref target="frus1932v05#pg_159">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1932, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">v</hi>, p. 159</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Foreign Minister was to have first discussion on proposal with the President this
                    afternoon after some days separate study.</p>
                <p>Foreign Minister has requested Brazilian Minister to transmit to Rio de Janeiro
                    the wish that Brazil advise Argentine and join with the United States Government
                    in the invitation to the other Republics for presentation of the formula.</p>
                <p>[Speaking] to the Argentine Minister, Bolivian Minister for Foreign Affairs was
                    opposed to suspension hostilities before the discussions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Des Portes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
